{"word":"δεῖνα","slug":"δεῖνα","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>δεῖνα, ὁ</el>/<el>ἡ</el>/<el>τό</el></b> [a formation developed from *<el>τάδε ἔνα</el> ‘this and that’ and present in <el>τὰ <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:δεῖνα\">δεῖνα</a></el>, hence the <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ gen.\">gen.</a> <el>τοῦ <a class=\"S\" href=\"S:δεῖνα\">δεῖνα</a></el> and associated inflection] ‘unnamed/unspecified entity’, <b><i>so-and-so</i> <a href='B:470 26:18'>Mt 26:18</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:δειλός\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:δεινός\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}